## Limitations

The findings are primarily based on reports and studies conducted during the COVID-19 pandemic, which may not fully capture the long-term trends in domestic violence. Additionally, variations in data collection methods and reporting standards across different regions may affect the comparability of the findings. Further research is needed to explore the ongoing impact of the pandemic on domestic violence and to develop effective intervention strategies.